A ward of the District of Columbia Government committed to the jurisdiction of the Child and Family Services Agency, or its successor agency, pursuant to section 11 of the Act to establish a Board of Public Welfare in and for the District of Columbia,
      to determine its functions, and for other purposes, approved March 16, 1926 (44 Stat. 210; D.C. Official Code § 4-114 (2008 Repl.)) and section 301a of the Prevention of Child Abuse and Neglect Act of 1977, effective April 4, 2001 (D.C. Law 13-277;
      D.C. Official Code § 4-1303.01a (2008 Repl.));
